  "body": "When running `buidler compile` from a global installation in the sample project with the Greeter contract, I'm getting the following error:\r\n```\r\n$ buidler compile --show-stack-traces\r\nAn unexpected error occurred: Cannot find module 'typescript'\r\n\r\nError: Cannot find module 'typescript'\r\n    at Function.Module._resolveFilename (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:580:15)\r\n    at Function.resolve (internal/modules/cjs/helpers.js:30:19)\r\n    at Object.register (/home/spalladino/.nvm/versions/node/v10.13.0/lib/node_modules/ts-node/src/index.ts:206:28)\r\n    at Object.<anonymous> (/home/spalladino/.nvm/versions/node/v10.13.0/lib/node_modules/ts-node/register/index.js:1:16)\r\n    at Module._compile (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:688:30)\r\n    at Object.Module._extensions..js (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:699:10)\r\n    at Module.load (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:598:32)\r\n    at tryModuleLoad (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:537:12)\r\n    at Function.Module._load (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:529:3)\r\n    at Module.require (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:636:17)\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that this does not happen if I run a locally installed buidler via `npx buidler compile`.\r\n\r\nEnvironment:\r\n- Ubuntu 18.10\r\n- Node v10.13.0\r\n- Buidler 1.0.0-beta.7",
